 black hole model. We argue\ninstead that Mrk~231 is the nearest example of weak-lined \"wind-dominated\"\nquasars with high Eddington ratios and geometrically thick (\"slim\") accretion\ndisks; these quasars are likely more common in the early universe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2016 20:10:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-06"}
