{"id":"1605.00709","submitter":"Vladimir Nikiforov","authors":"V. Nikiforov","title":"Hypergraphs and hypermatrices with symmetric spectrum","comments":"17 pages. Corrected proof on p. 13","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  It is well known that a graph is bipartite if and only if the spectrum of its\nadjacency matrix is symmetric. In the present paper, this assertion is\ndissected into three separate matrix results of wider scope, which are extended\nalso to hypermatrices. To this end the concept of bipartiteness is generalized\nby a new monotone property of cubical hypermatrices, called odd-colorable\nmatrices. It is shown that a nonnegative symmetric $r$-matrix $A$ has a\nsymmetric spectrum if and only if $r$ is even and $A$ is odd-colorable. This\nresult also solves a problem of Pearson and Zhang about hypergraphs with\nsymmetric spectrum and disproves a conjecture of Zhou, Sun, Wang, and Bu.\n  Separately, similar results are obtained for the $H$-spectram of\nhypermatrices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2016 23:51:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 18:49:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-11"}
